# Project Structure & Naming Conventions

Apply these conventions when creating or editing files in this repository.

## 1) Repository Shape (Current)
- Frontend is at repository root using `src/` (Vite app), not `frontend/`.
- Backend API is under `backend/` with its own runtime and dependencies.
- Database SQL/migrations currently live under `backend/database/`.
- Project docs are markdown files at root and optionally under `docs/`.
- Utility/maintenance scripts can live in `backend/scripts/` or root `scripts/`.

## 2) Backend Layering
- Prefer separation: `routes` -> `controllers` -> `services` -> `repositories/models`.
- Keep business logic in services, not routes.
- Keep DB query logic in repositories/models.
- Put cross-cutting logic in middlewares (auth, validation, logging).
- For this repo, keep backend changes inside `backend/` unless explicitly shared.

## 3) Frontend Organization
- Keep reusable UI in `src/components`.
- Keep API calls/client wrappers in `src/services` (or existing equivalent).
- Keep reusable data/state logic in `src/hooks`.
- Keep constants/types in dedicated files/folders under `src/`.
- Align with existing folder names first; avoid creating parallel patterns.

## 4) Naming Rules
- Files: kebab-case (example: `user-profile.ts`, `auth-middleware.ts`).
- React components: PascalCase (example: `UserCard.tsx`).
- Functions/variables: camelCase.
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE.
- Classes/interfaces/types: PascalCase.

## 5) Common File Patterns
- Backend: `*.controller.*`, `*.service.*`, `*.model.*`, `*.routes.*`, `*.middleware.*`
- Tests: `*.test.*` (unit/integration/e2e by folder if possible).
- DB migrations: timestamp/sequence prefixes (example: `20240101_001_create_users_table.sql`).
- Keep script filenames descriptive and action-oriented (example: `auto-assign-missing-production-orders.mjs`).

## 6) Imports & Modules
- Prefer clear module boundaries between frontend and backend.
- If FE/BE both need a contract, place it in shared modules instead of cross-importing app code.
- Prefer named exports over default exports unless framework convention requires otherwise.

## 7) Environment & Secrets
- Never commit real secrets.
- Keep sample values in `.env.example`.
- Use uppercase snake case for env keys.
- Frontend public env keys must use `VITE_*` in this repository.
- Backend env should stay in `backend/.env` and must not leak to frontend.

## 8) API Conventions
- Prefer plural resource names in REST paths.
- Avoid verbs in endpoint URLs.
- Keep response shapes consistent (`success`, `data`, `message`, optional `meta`).
- Keep error shapes consistent (`success: false`, `error.code`, `error.message`, optional `details`).

## 9) Git Conventions
- Branch names: `feature/*`, `fix/*`, `chore/*`, `hotfix/*`.
- Commit messages: Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `chore:`).

## 10) Practical Priority
- Follow existing local patterns first when the repository already has a clear convention.
- For new modules, use the conventions above.
- Do not refactor folder structure unless explicitly requested.
